# UDS Component Completeness Checklist

Every new UDS component must include ALL of the following before it is considered complete:

## CSS (`uds/components/{name}.css`)
- [ ] `:hover` state on interactive elements
- [ ] `:focus-visible` style with `--uds-color-border-outline-focus-visible` on all focusable elements
- [ ] `disabled` / `aria-disabled="true"` styling (if applicable)
- [ ] All colors, spacing, fonts, radii use UDS tokens (see `uds-token-first-css` rule)
- [ ] Shadow values use `--uds-shadow-*` tokens

## JS (`uds/components/{name}.js`) ŌĆö only when the component has interactive behavior
- [ ] IIFE pattern with `window.UDS._init{Name} = init{Name}`
- [ ] `_udsInit` guard (set AFTER validation, not before)
- [ ] Keyboard activation (Enter/Space) for any focusable interactive element
- [ ] Registered in `uds/uds.js` orchestrator COMPONENT_SCRIPTS array
- [ ] Registered in `UDS.init()` function with correct selector

## Spec ŌĆö JSON content (`content/{name}.json`)
This is the source of truth for the Guidelines tab. The renderer fills the tab automatically.
- [ ] Required minimum: `component`, `title`, `description`, `whenToUse`, `whenNotToUse`, `dependencies.css`, `accessibility.keyboard`, `owner`
- [ ] Aim for 80%+ spec completeness before marking Production Ready (see `uds-content-schema.mdc`)
- [ ] Add `figmaNodeId` if a deep-link to a specific variant exists
- [ ] Add `storybookSlug` once the Storybook story exists

## Documentation site (`index.html`)
- [ ] Sidebar link enabled (not `disabled` class)
- [ ] `<div data-page="{name}">` with title, description, tabbed navigation
- [ ] Examples tab with at least 2-3 example variants
- [ ] Code tab with vanilla HTML structure (Example only ŌĆö production code lives in Storybook)
- [ ] Guidelines tab is an EMPTY `<div data-tab-panel="guidelines"></div>` ŌĆö `renderGuidelines()` fills it from JSON
- [ ] Changelog tab (placeholder if no changes yet)
- [ ] Playground tab (empty div ŌĆö wired by app.js)
- [ ] DO NOT add Usage-tab style HTML inside the Guidelines panel ŌĆö edit the JSON instead

## App logic (`app.js`)
- [ ] `PLAYGROUNDS['{name}']` with controls array and `render(state)` returning `{ html, code }` (vanilla only ŌĆö no `reactCode`/`vueCode`)
  - All icon controls use `type: 'icon-search'`
- [ ] `IMPL_DATA['{name}']` with `cssFile`, `jsFunc`, `tokens`, `html()`
- [ ] `COMPONENT_STATUS['{name}']` with status and since version
- [ ] `FIGMA_LINKS['{name}']` with Figma node ID
- [ ] `CHANGELOG` entry under the current version with `category: "components"` and `component: "{name}"`
- [ ] `JS_FUNC_TO_FILE['{funcName}']` mapping (if component has JS)
- [ ] Component CSS and JS files added to the download ZIP `files` array

## Code quality (vanilla)
- [ ] All `udc-*` class names match the canonical BEM pattern
- [ ] All keyboard interactions in JS match the spec's `accessibility.keyboard` table
- [ ] Realistic data examples added if the component is data-consuming (Data Table, List, Dropdown, Search, Breadcrumb)
